**Doxee**** ****Workplace 2** is a web portal for end-to-end execution of interactive and collaborative document workflows. Business users can initiate these workflows, so-called Business Cases, and perform all necessary actions to complete them, from within the same interface.

Furthermore, the application provides user-friendly overviews of open workflows and pending user input, with extensive search and filtering options to facilitate process monitoring. In service-oriented environments, Workplace 2 can significantly speed up and automate the document creation and delivery process.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Workplace 1 vs. Workplace 2

With release 6.6, we presented a complete redesign of the previous Workplace 1 application. Workplace 2 features a new technology stack, a revamped UX, rewritten Human Tasks and other upgrades. While the core concept of both application versions is the same, due to the differences in technology, the information in this product guide is not valid for Workplace 1. Please refer to the separate Workplace 1 product documentation and to the [release notes of version 6.6](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-6-6) to find out how to transition to Workplace 2.

## Key capabilities
Workplace 2 is capable of conducting and managing large-scale customer communications workflows. Here are main capabilities:

- **CRM enhancement:** Facilitates tasks like managing technical support tickets, billing, and sending notifications

- **System integration:** Connects existing ERP and CRM systems, enabling document preview and workflow validation before dispatch

- **Personalized customer service:** Enriches one-on-one communication with customized data, offers, and quantitative insights

- **Customizable web portal:** Allows administrators to configure forms, add relevant data, and trigger approval workflows for document delivery

- **Granular access control:** Enables a precise mapping of privileges and responsibilities within workflows

## Prerequisites
Workplace 2 can be accessed through a web interface after logging into the Doxee suite of products. Make sure that you have the necessary user rights to be able to view and start Business Cases and work on tasks.

In order to access and use Workplace 2, its necessary to:

- Deploy and configure the Workplace 2 application

- Upload a Business Case definition

- Have user rights that allow to access and work on the Business Case

> User roles and access

User access to Workplace 2 and individual Workplace 2 areas is highly customizable. Some user roles, groups or individual users may be restricted from viewing certain Business Cases or performing certain actions. For example, an administrator may restrict the right to terminate a Business Case Instance to only certain user groups.

Business Cases are interactive processes which are started and completed from Workplace. A Business Case typically consists of one or several Human Tasks, which require user input in order to advance the process. An open Business Case is called a Business Case Instance.
